      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LILLY DUTTON (4) is yet to miss the placings in an excellent record this track and trip which boasts two wins. Recorded a 0.8 lengths win (23.46) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. Looks a leading chance on best. LINE AND SINKER (8) was strongly fancied last time and hit the ground running with a fast early split, paving the way for a one length win at this track over 300m in 16.97. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Expected to feature again. TINY BUT MIGHTY (1) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (23.78) at this track behind LILLY DUTTON in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Comes through a solid form race last start. Can feature again. LUCKY DROVER (2) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
